<br>
I'm an upper-middle class white american.  My parents made an ok amount of money, but we weren't rich by any stretch of the imagination.  Being able to afford college was going to be hell.  Of course I took out a loan, but I would rather have gotten scholarships.<br>
<br>
I pulled down list after list of potential scholarships I could get.  I would say 80% of them were for a distinct race other than caucasian (American Indian, black, asian, etc.).  The rest of them were divided up into 2 sections.  Disabled and not.  Then the like...20 scholarships left I had to choose from I was ineligible for either due to GPA (graduated 3.49 w/honors, most req'd 3.5...ain't that a bitch?), activities in school (like sports =P), and low-income ( &lt; 24k/year or something).  I was in the band, so I tried for like 2 of them, but got shot down both times.<br>
<br>
This was how my search went.  I was lucky that the school band gave away a $500 scholarship for books for outstanding players.  Having been there all 4 years and been 1st chair trombone all 4, there were few others in the way of choices (only 1 other guy).  I won it...and of course all that money went away the first semester of books I bought lol.  <br>
